03:26.473 --> 03:29.067
Hey, uh, hey, kid,
where you been?

03:33.147 --> 03:35.047
Kid?

03:35.182 --> 03:36.809
Well, well,
whatever your name is.

03:36.950 --> 03:38.440
L-Look, you got
to fix our limousine.

03:38.585 --> 03:40.713
This kid is on a break.

03:43.991 --> 03:45.982
(slow ballad plays)

03:52.032 --> 03:53.363
Get a load of that kid.

03:53.500 --> 03:55.298
That hood's got some nerve.

03:55.435 --> 03:56.869
Yeah.

03:57.004 --> 03:58.563
Don't worry, boss.
I'll take care of him.

03:58.705 --> 03:59.968
- Sit down, Hinstead.
- Right, boss.

04:00.107 --> 04:01.666
Let me handle this.

04:01.809 --> 04:03.470
Excuse me, sir?

04:03.610 --> 04:05.305
Sir. That's very nice.

04:05.445 --> 04:07.470
What can I do for you?

04:07.614 --> 04:09.241
Well, look, I'm terribly sorry
to bother you,

04:09.383 --> 04:11.477
but, uh, do girls always
run to you like this?

04:11.618 --> 04:14.019
I got to tell you,
this crowd is, uh, slow.

04:14.154 --> 04:15.485
Usually, they jump.

04:15.622 --> 04:18.557
Well, I want to tell you
that, uh,

04:18.692 --> 04:20.023
I'm a Hollywood talent scout.

04:20.160 --> 04:21.286
Oh, no. Thanks very much,

04:21.428 --> 04:23.920
but I discovered all the talent
I need right here.

04:24.064 --> 04:25.361
Oh, no. (laughs)

04:25.499 --> 04:27.490
No. no. no, no.

04:29.069 --> 04:30.935
I, uh...

04:31.071 --> 04:32.334
I-I don't think you understand.

04:32.472 --> 04:34.031
You see, I've been combing
the country

04:34.174 --> 04:36.108
for America's new James Dean.

04:36.243 --> 04:38.041
James Dean.
Now, that's important.

04:38.178 --> 04:40.203
I'll have your limo ready
in an hour, Jack.

04:40.347 --> 04:41.644
Now, wait, wait.

04:41.782 --> 04:43.181
Now, I...
I've been watching you,

04:43.317 --> 04:45.285
and I think you've got a lot
of potential.

04:45.419 --> 04:47.183
I mean, you could be
the next James Dean,

04:47.321 --> 04:48.618
the hottest star
in this country.

04:48.755 --> 04:51.918
Couldn't we have this convo
when I finish my dance?

04:52.059 --> 04:54.050
I'm serious.

04:54.194 --> 04:55.958
No, look, I'm serious. I...

04:56.096 --> 04:57.291
Aren't you excited?

04:57.431 --> 04:58.592
Hey, look at this.

04:58.732 --> 05:01.326
Anybody's excited
with a few minutes with Daphne.

05:03.770 --> 05:05.636
This guy is really cool.

05:05.772 --> 05:08.207
I mean, did you see the way
the girls run up to him

05:08.342 --> 05:09.832
when he snaps his fingers?

05:09.977 --> 05:11.604
I mean, this guy has magic!

05:11.745 --> 05:14.180
Hey, good. He'll be able to fix
our limo like that.

05:14.314 --> 05:15.543
Forget the car.

05:15.682 --> 05:18.743
Hinstead, I think we've stumbled
onto a major new talent.

05:18.886 --> 05:20.615
HOWARD:
<i>I</i> don't see

05:20.754 --> 05:22.779
<i>why you don't want to go
to the convention.</i>

05:22.923 --> 05:26.689
Dad, I'm sorry, but this is
my last summer before college,

05:26.827 --> 05:28.295
and I've got to do
something big.

05:28.428 --> 05:29.759
I've got to do
something exciting,

05:29.897 --> 05:31.956
and that's why I can't go
to the Leopard Convention.

05:32.099 --> 05:34.067
What's wrong
with the Leopard Convention?

05:34.201 --> 05:36.829
Well, I'll tell you
what's wrong with it.

05:36.970 --> 05:39.837
Leopards, Leopards,
we are true.

05:39.973 --> 05:43.238
We won't change our spots
for you.

05:47.180 --> 05:50.343
Dad, that is not my idea
of exciting.

05:50.484 --> 05:52.350
Well, of course
it's not exciting!

05:52.486 --> 05:53.544
You forgot to growl.

05:53.687 --> 05:55.246
(growls)

05:55.389 --> 05:57.585
What are you trying
to do to me, anyway?

05:57.724 --> 05:59.419
It'll be a fun
family vacation.

05:59.559 --> 06:00.993
What-what vacation, Dad?

06:01.128 --> 06:02.186
It's here in Milwaukee.

06:02.329 --> 06:04.627
Oh. Marion. Mar... tell him.

06:04.765 --> 06:06.028
Tell him!

06:06.166 --> 06:07.361
Richie's right!

06:11.138 --> 06:14.005
Howard Cunningham,
I have something to say.

06:14.141 --> 06:15.165
Oh.

06:15.309 --> 06:17.641
We have scrimped and saved
all year!

06:17.778 --> 06:20.338
Now, we didn't do this
to go to downtown Milwaukee.

06:20.480 --> 06:21.504
- That's right, Dad.
- Yeah.

06:21.648 --> 06:23.377
How can I tell my mother
we went on vacation,

06:23.517 --> 06:25.212
and we spent 80 cents for gas?

06:26.420 --> 06:28.445
And that's if we take
the long way!

06:28.588 --> 06:30.249
-(overlapping chatter)
- I don't care, Marion.

06:30.390 --> 06:32.358
Every summer,
we go to the conven...

06:32.492 --> 06:34.483
Low.

06:36.163 --> 06:38.291
Now, you all know
my cousin Chachi.

06:38.432 --> 06:39.763
There's your little boyfriend.

06:39.900 --> 06:42.130
- Hold your breath.
-(Richie laughs)

06:43.170 --> 06:44.695
How you doing, blue eyes?

06:44.838 --> 06:46.636
What are you selling today,
shrimp?

06:46.773 --> 06:49.037
Oh, no. I sold all the shrimp
to Alfred.

06:49.176 --> 06:52.612
But for you,
I got no-smear lipstick.

06:52.746 --> 06:54.646
We can test it out later.

06:54.781 --> 06:56.772
Wah, wah, wah.

06:58.852 --> 07:01.014
Yeah. I-l beg
your indulgence, Mr. C.

07:01.154 --> 07:02.918
Uh, we're not here
to make you out.

07:03.056 --> 07:04.546
We're not here to sell.

07:04.691 --> 07:06.159
The reason
I brought Chachi along

07:06.293 --> 07:08.489
is 'cause he's got
some very hot info.

07:08.628 --> 07:09.720
Take it away.

07:09.863 --> 07:11.194
Oh, yeah, really hot.

07:11.331 --> 07:13.265
(loudly):
Ladies and gentlemen!

07:13.400 --> 07:14.868
Shy little fellow.

07:15.002 --> 07:17.403
My cousin,
the one and only Fonz...

07:17.537 --> 07:18.766
That's me.

07:18.905 --> 07:20.930
...got discovered
by a talent scout at Arnold's,

07:21.074 --> 07:22.803
and he's going to Hollywood!

07:22.943 --> 07:24.536
- Oh, that's amazing!
- Oh! Oh, goodness.

07:24.678 --> 07:26.305
- Wonderful!
- That's great!

07:26.446 --> 07:29.438
Kids, imagine,
I have cooked veggies

07:29.583 --> 07:32.109
for a Hollywood star.

07:32.252 --> 07:33.845
Well, this is all very exciting,

07:33.987 --> 07:36.081
but why is Chachi
telling us this?

07:36.223 --> 07:38.317
Modesty wouldn't allow me.

07:40.527 --> 07:42.552
Of course I'll be keeping an eye
on the garage

07:42.696 --> 07:43.754
while Fonzie's gone.

07:43.897 --> 07:46.730
Chach, this is my moment,
not yours.

07:46.867 --> 07:48.392
Hey, is it really true?

07:48.535 --> 07:50.401
Oh, yeah. He's not a star yet,

07:50.537 --> 07:53.404
but he will be after they make
a screen test in Hollywood.

07:53.540 --> 07:54.735
Ah, just a formality.

07:56.043 --> 07:58.375
CHACHI:
Have fun in Hollywood, Fonz.

07:58.512 --> 08:00.105
Catch you later, blue eyes.

08:00.247 --> 08:01.612
That'll be the day.

08:01.748 --> 08:03.716
Oh. Oh, Arthur.

08:03.850 --> 08:05.750
You don't need a screen test.

08:05.886 --> 08:09.584
You will be a star
the minute they see you.

08:11.858 --> 08:13.155
(doorbell rings)

08:13.293 --> 08:15.284
Come in.

08:23.437 --> 08:24.871
Oh, hi, Ralph. Hi, Potsie.

08:25.005 --> 08:26.996
They recognized us.

08:28.308 --> 08:29.901
Rich, you're not
gonna believe it.

08:30.043 --> 08:31.374
Pots and I here are going

08:31.511 --> 08:33.342
to Hollywood tomorrow
with the Fonz.

08:33.480 --> 08:36.142
D-Da-Dad,
they're going to Hollywood!

08:36.283 --> 08:37.250
RALPH:
You bet.

08:37.384 --> 08:39.078
Our last big fling, Rich.

08:39.219 --> 08:41.950
Da-Dad, our last big fling!

08:42.089 --> 08:44.615
Ralph, why are you carrying
an ironing board?

08:44.758 --> 08:46.157
I took off the legs.

08:46.293 --> 08:47.920
Now it's a surf board.

08:48.061 --> 08:49.529
Oh! Da-Dad, did you hear that?

08:49.663 --> 08:50.721
He's gonna be surfing.

08:50.864 --> 08:53.424
Hey, I just got a flash.

08:53.567 --> 08:56.696
Why don't the Cunningham brood
hop a ride

08:56.837 --> 09:00.330
on my trip to stardom?

09:00.474 --> 09:02.704
On behalf of the family,
I accept.

09:02.843 --> 09:06.336
(overlapping chatter
and exclamations)

09:06.480 --> 09:08.073
Now, wait a minute.

09:08.215 --> 09:09.410
- Wait a minute!
-(group quiets)

09:09.549 --> 09:11.017
Now, the convention starts
tomorrow,

09:11.151 --> 09:13.347
and I've already donated
the dust pans!

09:13.487 --> 09:15.683
Oh, Howard, come on now!

09:15.822 --> 09:17.381
Think about this!

09:17.524 --> 09:18.958
Now, we're a democratic family.

09:19.092 --> 09:20.184
We want to go!

09:20.327 --> 09:22.523
Marion, I'm going
to be the Exalted Keeper

09:22.662 --> 09:24.653
of the Leopard Lodge!

09:24.798 --> 09:26.129
Joanie, Joanie,
this is for Hollywood.

09:26.266 --> 09:28.064
Show your dimples.

09:28.201 --> 09:30.397
Don't you understand?

09:30.537 --> 09:33.302
That's the first step
to becoming the Grand Poobah.

09:34.808 --> 09:37.140
And a man has got to do
what he's got to do.

09:37.277 --> 09:39.143
And I'm gonna do
what I got to do.

09:40.614 --> 09:42.844
And we're gonna go
to California.

09:42.983 --> 09:44.917
(cheering, screaming,
indistinct chatter)

09:45.051 --> 09:47.611
