- Yeah. -Now, here's the script
for your screen test.

10:24.324 --> 10:26.292
Now, study it and learn
the lines by tomorrow.

10:26.426 --> 10:27.450
The test is at 8:00.

10:27.594 --> 10:28.618
Oh, he'll-he'll be ready.

10:28.762 --> 10:30.252
Uh, the limousine will be here
at 6:00.

10:30.397 --> 10:32.729
Hey, who am I making
a movie with, roosters?

10:32.866 --> 10:33.958
(chuckles)

10:34.100 --> 10:35.795
Come on, you'll need
some makeup.

10:35.936 --> 10:37.233
Makeup?
Hey, let me tell you something.

10:37.370 --> 10:39.338
I'm supposed to be the new
James Dean, not the new...

10:39.472 --> 10:40.530
(in high-pitched voice):
Natalie Wood.

10:40.674 --> 10:42.301
(chuckles)

10:42.442 --> 10:44.376
Well, she has to get up at 5:00.

10:44.511 --> 10:46.104
Now, the limo will be here
at 6:00.

10:46.246 --> 10:48.908
- Now, you got to be ready.
- HINSTEAD: Hey, boss?

10:49.049 --> 10:52.383
Hey, I'll tell you,
it ain't easy being a star.

10:53.887 --> 10:56.185
Well, what do you think
of it, huh?

10:56.323 --> 11:00.317
Oh, Mr. C, that is
a beauty of a shirt.

11:00.460 --> 11:02.087
- Yeah?
- What did you do, plug it in?

11:02.229 --> 11:03.458
(Richie chuckles)

11:03.597 --> 11:05.759
I'm kidding. I'm kidding.
I was just kidding.

11:05.899 --> 11:07.663
It's nice. It's nice, Dad.

11:07.801 --> 11:09.098
Yeah. Thanks.

11:09.236 --> 11:10.931
One out of two isn't bad.

11:11.071 --> 11:12.095
Nice shirt.

11:12.239 --> 11:13.832
Oh, thank you.

11:13.974 --> 11:17.137
Uh, look, I-I-I want to see
if I can find that, uh...

11:17.277 --> 11:18.438
that drugstore.

11:18.578 --> 11:21.070
You know, the one where
Lana Turner was discovered in?

11:21.214 --> 11:23.876
I, uh... I got to buy
some suntan lotion.

11:34.828 --> 11:36.990
Yeah, I see where it is.
Yeah.

11:37.130 --> 11:39.292
Say, uh, listen,
I read in <i>Life</i> magazine

11:39.432 --> 11:41.901
that most of the Hollywood stars
stay in those cottages

11:42.035 --> 11:43.594
at the Beverly Hills Hotel.

11:43.737 --> 11:45.535
Oh, that's not true,
Mr. Cunningham.

11:45.672 --> 11:48.107
No? Well, they wouldn't stay at
a place like this, would they?

11:48.241 --> 11:50.266
- Sure, they would.
- Why?

11:50.410 --> 11:51.673
Because this is better.

11:51.811 --> 11:53.609
Besides, it's near the beach.

11:53.747 --> 11:55.613
- Oh, yeah. Maybe you're right.
-(Duvall chuckles)

11:55.749 --> 11:56.910
Excuse me.

11:57.050 --> 11:59.109
Could you, uh, tell me
where I check in?

11:59.252 --> 12:00.981
Oh, yeah, the lobby
is right through that arch

12:01.121 --> 12:02.179
and to your right.

12:02.322 --> 12:03.585
Right through the arch
and to the right?

12:03.723 --> 12:04.918
Uh-huh.

12:05.058 --> 12:07.049
That's a beauty of a shirt.

12:08.061 --> 12:10.052
Oh, thank you.
Thank you.

12:11.698 --> 12:13.826
Hey, isn't that Lorne Greene?

12:13.967 --> 12:16.902
Lorne Greene?
At the Hollywood Palms?

12:17.037 --> 12:19.028
(laughs)

12:23.143 --> 12:24.941
Hi, Dad. Bye, Dad.
I'm going to the beach.

12:25.078 --> 12:26.512
Just a minute, young lady.

12:26.646 --> 12:28.239
I'd like to see
your bathing suit.

12:28.381 --> 12:30.816
- Can't I just tell you about it?
- Let's see it.

12:33.787 --> 12:35.653
Straps are nice.

12:35.789 --> 12:38.815
Now, you get back in there and
put on the rest of that suit.

12:38.958 --> 12:40.722
Uh, Mother said
it was all right.

12:40.860 --> 12:42.726
Marion!

12:42.862 --> 12:44.091
Mar...

12:45.198 --> 12:46.495
Now...

12:53.473 --> 12:57.103
Now, that's what I call
a decent bathing suit.

12:57.243 --> 12:59.268
Marion, did you see Joanie?

